From be185128085529e070b38fc3d89d674f58db46cb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: David Allsopp <david.allsopp@metastack.com>
Date: Sat, 10 Apr 2021 15:04:07 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] Generate ld.conf using relative paths

(cherry picked from commit 480279ecd68023a12b75c43706d0160f83f69c07)

diff --git a/Changes b/Changes
index 3267ba7e2e47261ca913594eefdc9752fc22ef4b..1ca240dd056cb48c687d2cee3382619dc93b0aa1 100644
--- a/Changes
+++ b/Changes
@@ -17,8 +17,10 @@ OCaml 4.14 maintenance version
 
 * #14???: Explicit relative paths in ld.conf (".", "..", "./<path...>",
   "../<path...>") are interpreted as being relative to the directory ld.conf
-  was loaded from. The brave may continue to put implicit paths in ld.conf. The
-  interpretation of CAML_LD_LIBRARY_PATH is unaltered.
+  was loaded from, and the default ld.conf now uses relative paths, rather than
+  embedding the absolute path to the Standard Library. The brave may continue to
+  put implicit paths in ld.conf. The interpretation of CAML_LD_LIBRARY_PATH is
+  unaltered.
   (David Allsopp, review by ???)
 
